environment.model

Class Station

  • java.lang.Object
    • environment.model.Station

  • public class Station
extends java.lang.Object
    Encapsulates the behaviour of a collection of Locations. This station has toString() which returns a data structure used by the views to output the simulation to the user. This station stores and relocates RoadUsers between its locations.
    Version:
    27/04/2017
    Author:
    Joshua_Eddy
    See Also:
    enter(RoadUser), clone(), addLocation(Location), getFuelProfit(), getLostFuelProfit(), getNumberOfLoactions(), getSalesProfit(), getLostSalesProfit(), getRoadUsersRejected(), getNumberOfRoadUsers(), environment.GUI, RoadUser, Location, LinkedList, HashMap

      • toMove

        private java.util.Map<RoadUser,Location> toMove
        Contains the RoadUsers that need to be moved to the a new Location. The key for this HashMap is the RoadUser as this will be unique because the same RoadUser should not be require to move to two separate Locationss at the same time. The value of this HashMap is the current Location the key RoadUser is in.
        See Also:
        HashMap, RoadUser, Location

      • processLocations

        public void processLocations()
        Iterate through all of the Locations that make up the Station and cause them to process their respective queues. If a RoadUser is required to be moved to another Location then it will be assuming there is enough space for it in its next Location.

        private boolean move(RoadUser roadUser,
                     java.lang.Class<? extends Location> nextLocation)
        Moves the specified RoadUser's next Location. If that location is null then it is removed from the station.
        Parameters:
        roadUser - The RoadUser to be relocated its next Location.
        nextLocation - The Class of the next Location of the specified RoadUser.
        Returns:
        boolean whether the RoadUser was added to its next location or removed from the station.
